For DevOps and EC2, SSH is the primary tool for Linux instances, AWS Systems Manager is preferred for secure access without opening ports, and RDP is used for Windows servers.

Why is it best?
Secure (key-based authentication)
Lightweight & fast
Works perfectly with automation (scripts, CI/CD)
Industry standard



Use Case	                Best Tool
Linux EC2	                SSH (OpenSSH)
Secure enterprise access	AWS Systems Manager
Windows EC2	              RDP
